This directory contains interactive modal logic worksheets used with
lecture notes for an intermediate logic course.

## Main Files

- `index.html` — worksheet of satisfiability / comparison problems
- `non-entailment.html` — worksheet of non-entailment problems
- `worksheet-common.js` — shared worksheet logic used by both pages
- `DEVELOPER-NOTES.md` — implementation notes and local testing tips

## Modal Logic Playground

The worksheets embed and slightly modify the
[Modal Logic Playground](https://github.com/rkirsling/modallogic) by
Ross Kirsling, used under the MIT License (see `modallogic/LICENSE`).

Local changes include:

- uppercase propositional variable labels (`P`, `Q`, ...)
- small keybinding/focus tweaks for iframe embedding
- trace-aware evaluation support in `modallogic/js/MPL.js`

## Running Locally

Serve the repo over HTTP rather than opening the HTML files directly:

```powershell
python -m http.server 8766 --bind 127.0.0.1
```

Then open, for example:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:8766/kripke-worksheet/non-entailment.html
```
